<body>
    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 2839: Check if Strings Can be Made Equal With Operations I (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given two strings a and b of the same length. You can perform the following operations on string
                a: swap positions 0 and 2, or swap positions 1 and 3. Return true if you can make string a equal to
                string b by performing these operations any number of times, false otherwise.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: a = "abcd", b = "cdab"<br>
                Output: true<br>
                Explanation: After swapping (0,2) to get "cbad" and then (1,3) to get "cdab", string a equals b.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool canBeEqual(string a, string b) {
        if (a == b) return true;
        // case 1: swap (0,2)
        swap(a[0], a[2]);
        if (a == b) return true;
        swap(a[0], a[2]); // revert
        // case 2: swap (1,3)
        swap(a[1], a[3]);
        if (a == b) return true;
        // case 3: swap both pairs
        swap(a[0], a[2]);
        return a == b;
    }
};</code></pre>
        </div>
